# Documentation Rules

## Source of truth

SPEC.md is the canonical document. All other docs derive from it. If there's a conflict, SPEC.md wins.

## Editing principles

- These are living documents — updates are expected and welcome.
- Never change the core principles (no comments/likes/DMs, cooperative ownership, community-first entry) without explicit user approval.
- Keep the tone: warm, direct, slightly rebellious. Not corporate, not startup.
- Speeches (CREATOR-SPEECH.md, LAUNCH-SPEECH.md) are written to be spoken aloud. Keep them conversational.

## Structure

- SPEC.md — vision, identity, features, strategy, open questions
- ROADMAP.md — timelines, subsidies, legal, admin
- STATUS.md — current phase, decisions made, action plan
- Speeches — pitch materials for live delivery
